PHASE 2: INDUSTRIALIZATION (Years 4-10)

A. Population Growth Curve

Year Population Births Earth Arrivals Key Milestone
4 50 0 38 First Martian manufacturing
5 120 2 70 Propellant export begins
6 250 5 130 First child born on Mars
7 450 10 200 Robotic self-replication achieved
8 750 20 300 First surgical suite operational
9 1,200 35 450 University classes begin
10 2,000 60 800 Economic surplus achieved

B. ISRU Industries Development

Tier 1: Survival Essentials (Years 1-3)

· Water ice mining and purification
· Oxygen production (electrolysis)
· Basic Marscrete for expansion

Tier 2: Industrial Base (Years 4-6)

· Metallurgy: Molten regolith electrolysis → Fe, Al, Si, Mg
· Basalt Fiber: Melt extrusion → structural elements, textiles
· Chemical Industry: Sulfur processing, polymer production
· Electronics: Silicon purification, simple chip fabrication

Tier 3: Advanced Manufacturing (Years 7-10)

· Machine Shop: CNC fabrication of replacement parts
· Ceramics: High-temperature materials from local clays
· Pharmaceuticals: Algae-based drug production
· Bio-plastics: Genetically engineered bacteria

C. Economic Model

Exports (To Earth/Moon/Orbit):

1. Propellant: LOX/CH₄ - $500/kg (vs $10,000/kg from Earth)
2. Data: Martian science, engineering IP - $100M/year
3. Materials: Rare isotopes, unique Mars materials - TBD
4. Tourism: Virtual reality experiences - $50M/year

Imports (From Earth):

1. High-Tech Electronics: Processors, sensors, specialized equipment
2. Genetics: Seed banks, bacterial cultures, medical supplies
3. Luxuries: Spices, fabrics, personal items
4. Personnel: Specialized experts on 5-year contracts

Internal Economy:

· Labor Credit System: All citizens receive basic income in "Martian Hours"
· Specialization Bonus: Critical skills earn 2-3× multiplier
· Innovation Rewards: Patent-like system for Mars-specific inventions
· Land Allocation: Residential/Commercial space as function of contribution

D. Expansion Protocol

Tunnel Growth Rate:

· Year 1-3: 500m/year (human-directed Vitreous Mole)
· Year 4-6: 2km/year (semi-autonomous Moles)
· Year 7-10: 5km/year (fully autonomous fleet)

New Settlement Creation:

1. Prospecting: Identify new lava tube within 50km
2. Robotic Prep: Deploy mini-fleet for 12-month preparation
3. Human Migration: 100-200 volunteers establish new "neighborhood"
4. Connection: High-speed pressurized transit tunnel (5m diameter)

