PHASE 3: SURFACE CANOPY (Years 11-20)

A. Surface Structure Philosophy

Design Principles:

1. Non-Critical: All surface structures have subsurface backup
2. Specialized: Each structure serves a specific surface-advantage purpose
3. Connected: Pressurized access to subsurface at all points
4. Hardened: Designed for dust storm survival

B. Surface Infrastructure Matrix

Structure Purpose Size Pressure Connection Depth
Agriculture Domes Food production, psychology 100m diameter × 50m 70 kPa -10m access tunnel
Solar Farms Supplemental power 1km² arrays Martian ambient Surface cables
Landing Complex Cargo/Personnel arrival 5km from main hab Airlock system -15m garage
Observatory Astronomy, planetary science 30m dome 70 kPa lab, vacuum scope -20m operations center
Sports/Recreation Physical health, social cohesion 200m track field 70 kPa -5m locker rooms
Manufacturing Domes Large-scale fabrication 150m diameter 50 kPa (fire-safe) -15m raw material feed

C. Transportation Network

Subsurface:

· Personal Transit: Electric carts in 4m diameter tunnels
· Cargo System: Automated guided vehicles in 6m diameter tunnels
· High-Speed: Magnetic levitation in 8m diameter deep tunnels (100 km/h)

Surface:

· Pressurized Rovers: For crew transport (10km range)
· Cargo Haulers: Unpressurized for bulk materials
· Construction Equipment: Modified Earth machinery with CO₂ scrubbers

Orbital:

· Mars Ascent Vehicle: Reusable, methane-fueled (12-person capacity)
· Orbital Station: Transfer point for Earth arrivals
· Fuel Depot: LOX/CH₄ storage for deep-space missions

D. Population Distribution (Year 20)

Area Population Density (people/km²) Primary Function
Main Citadel 3,000 150 Governance, industry, research
Northern Settlement 1,200 120 Agriculture, light manufacturing
Western Research 500 50 Science, observatory operations
Eastern Industrial 800 80 Propellant production, mining
Orbital Station 100 N/A Transit, ship maintenance
Surface Canopies 400 20 Agriculture, recreation

