RISK MANAGEMENT FRAMEWORK

A. Catastrophic Risk Matrix

Risk Probability (Year 1-10) Impact Mitigation Strategy
Major Pressure Loss 0.5%/year Catastrophic Nested Egg design, sector isolation, emergency shelters
SMR Failure 1%/year Critical Dual reactors 500m apart, surface solar backup
Water System Contamination 5%/year Severe Triple redundancy, UV/ozone/filtration, 180-day reserve
Psychological Breakdown 10%/year High Pre-screening, continuous monitoring, VR therapy, Earth contact
Dust Storm Power Loss 100% (every 3 years) Moderate Nuclear primary, surface systems storm-hardened
Seismic Event 2%/year Variable Site selection away from faults, flexible couplings
Epidemic 3%/year Severe Medical quarantine capability, gene bank for antibodies

B. Redundancy Philosophy

Rule of Three:

1. Primary System: State-of-the-art, high efficiency
2. Backup System: Different technology, lower efficiency
3. Emergency System: Simple, robust, can be fabricated locally

Example: Oxygen Supply

· Primary: Water electrolysis (high efficiency)
· Backup: MOXIE-style CO₂ reduction (medium efficiency)
· Emergency: Chemical oxygen candles (low efficiency, 30-day supply)

C. Emergency Protocols

Shelter-in-Place Scenarios:

· Dust storm: 30-day provisions in each residential cluster
· Radiation event: Designated deep shelters with 10m rock cover
· Contamination: Isolation wards with independent life support

Evacuation Scenarios:

· Partial pressure loss: Move to adjacent sector through airlocks
· Complete habitat loss: Surface ascent vehicles to orbital station
· Planetary emergency: Earth return vehicles always fueled and ready

