APPENDICES

Appendix A: Technology Readiness Timeline

· TRL 9 technologies available now (life support basics, rockets)
· TRL 6-8 by 2030 (autonomous robots, compact reactors)
· TRL 4-5 by 2035 (plasma boring, Marscrete optimization)
· TRL 2-3 by 2040 (full robotic self-replication)

Appendix B: Mass Budget Analysis

· Total Earth-launched mass: 850 tons (robots + initial supplies)
· Mars-produced mass by Year 10: 50,000+ tons (expanded habitat, infrastructure)
· Economic break-even: Year 15 (exports exceed Earth imports)

Appendix C: Human Health Management

· Radiation exposure limits: <100 mSv/year (vs 1,000 mSv on surface)
· Bone/muscle loss countermeasures: Daily centrifuge, pharmaceutical
· Psychological support: VR nature experiences, Earth contact, meaningful work

Appendix D: Environmental Impact Assessment

· Subsurface minimal impact: No surface scarring
· Ice mining: Controlled, sustainable extraction
· Waste management: 99% recycling, sterile storage of residuals

Appendix E: First 100-Day Human Schedule

· Day 1-7: Systems familiarization, pressure check
· Day 8-30: First expansion tunnel initiation
· Day 31-60: Agricultural scale-up
· Day 61-100: First manufacturing from Martian materials

